Freelancer                -


                                     AGREEMENT FOR SERVICE


This Agreement for Service for Freelancer (“Agreement”) is entered into and made effective as of (“Effective Date”), at Kochi Kerala, by and


BETWEEN


D’WELL INFORMATICS AND SERVICES PRIVATE LIMITED

U72200KL1995PTC008931, a company registered in India with its principal office at H-10,  Kasthurba Nagar, Kadavanthra, Kochi - 682020 Kerala, India of Pan Number AAACD8274E and GSTIN 32AAACD8274E1ZW ("D’Well" including its successors and permitted assigns);


And


, an individual, with a principal place of business at , India of Pan Number

Mobile -     Email  -

Service offered -     

 (“Supplier”).

(Together the "Parties" or individually a "Party" are duly authorised to enter into the present Agreement.)

Whereas:

  1. D’Well has a need for Translation and Project Management Services; and

  2. The supplier has an interest in performing such services for D’Well; and

  3. The Parties wish to set forth the terms and conditions upon which such services will be provided to D’Well.


The Supplier is a Freelancer with the right of working for multiple clients and D’Well intends to engage the Supplier to provide services, the scope of which may be agreed upon from time to time between the Parties under this Agreement. In consideration of the foregoing, and the mutual promises herein contained, the Parties hereby agree as follows:


1. Description of Services


The Supplier will perform the Services and deliver Deliverables for D’Well and/or its clients. D’Well does not commit to purchasing Services from the Supplier, however, during the term of this Agreement, D’Well and/or its clients may request the Supplier to perform Additional Services which may be agreed upon and signed by both Parties. Such Additional Services shall be subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, in addition to any additional terms and conditions set forth. The Initial Services and Additional Services, if any, shall be referred to collectively in this Agreement as the “Services” comprising but not limited to:

Translations, taking interviews, fixing appointments, recording and editing videos/audios, proofreading, transcription, report writing and preparing presentations.


Notwithstanding any other clause of this Agreement, the Supplier agrees to perform the Services in accordance with the requirements of:

(a) all laws, rules and regulations and generally accepted industry standards that apply to the performance of the Services;

(b) the Code of Conduct and the Code of Practice of the Services under this Agreement in the respective country and the other countries wherever the project is executed; and

(c) the provisions of D’Well’s Interactions With Professionals Policy relating to the Services.


The Supplier will contact and deliver Services under this Agreement to D’Well and/or its clients while using the email ID provided by D’Well and/or its clients only, with a carbon copy to Project in charge.


2. Deliverables


Deliverables are the tangible things that the Supplier is expected to deliver to D’Well under this Agreement. They may include and not be limited to, information of web design files, reports, presentations, translations, interviewing information, schedule of appointments, video/audio recordings, proofreadings and transcriptions.


3. Term


This Agreement commences on the Effective Date and will continue for the later of  three years (3 years) or the completion of all Services by the Supplier unless terminated earlier in accordance with any clause, term or part of this Agreement and/or otherwise.


4. Pricing/Rates


The Supplier agrees to fulfil the milestones stated by D’Well and/or its clients, if the Supplier doesn’t meet the obligation or deliver the Services as under the order for each project on time, then D’Well will have some recourse or leeway as under this Agreement.
